Oil price, on Tuesday plummeted to $99.98 a barrel, the lowest in the last three weeks. The global oil benchmark, Brent crude, fell by over 6 percent to trade at $99.98 a barrel.  West Texas Intermediate witnessed a corresponding increase of over 6 percent at $96.31 a barrel. The price of crude had last Monday increased to $130 a barrel, the highest since 2008 as the United States and its European allies considered banning the importation of Russian oil in protest against Russiaâ€™s invasion of Ukraine. Russia is the world's second-largest oil producer, which mainly sells crude to European refineries, and is the largest supplier of natural gas to Europe, providing about 35% of its supply.